<body>

  <header>
    <h1>Spaghetti Carbonara</h1>
    <p>A quick, creamy, and delicious Italian pasta dish you can make in under 30 minutes.</p>
  </header>

  <main>

    <section>
      <h2>Time</h2>
      <p><strong>Prep Time:</strong> 10 minutes</p>
      <p><strong>Cook Time:</strong> 15 minutes</p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Ingredients</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>200g spaghetti</li>
        <li>100g pancetta or bacon</li>
        <li>2 eggs</li>
        <li>50g grated Parmesan cheese</li>
        <li>2 cloves garlic (optional)</li>
        <li>Salt and black pepper</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Instructions</h2>
      <ol>
        <li>Boil the spaghetti in salted water until al dente.</li>
        <li>In a pan, cook the pancetta until crispy. Add garlic if using.</li>
        <li>In a bowl, beat the eggs and mix in the Parmesan.</li>
        <li>Drain the pasta and return it to the pot (off the heat).</li>
        <li>Quickly stir in the pancetta and egg mixture, allowing the heat from the pasta to cook the eggs and create a creamy sauce.</li>
        <li>Season with salt and freshly ground black pepper. Serve immediately.</li>
      </ol>
    </section>

    <aside>
      <blockquote>
        Tip: Don't put the pot back on the stove after adding the eggs — you’ll scramble them instead of getting a creamy sauce!
      </blockquote>
    </aside>

    <section>
      <h2>Nutritional Facts (Approx.)</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>Calories: 550</li>
        <li>Protein: 22g</li>
        <li>Carbs: 60g</li>
        <li>Fat: 25g</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

  </main>

  <footer>
    <p>Recipe by Chef Marie © 2025</p>
  </footer>

</body>
